# Caracal Playbooks

Caracal Playbooks are copy-paste guides for using Caracal with coding agents. They help your agent integrate SDKs and review a Caracal codebase for compliance.

Use them inside your own project. You do not need the Caracal repository in your app.

## Layers

| Layer | Use it for |
| --- | --- |
| `sdks` | Integrating Caracal SDKs into your application. |
| `compliance` | Running a compliance and operations review of a Caracal codebase. |

## Supported agents

Each layer includes guides for:

- Claude Code
- GitHub Copilot
- OpenAI Codex

## How to use

1. Open the layer that matches what you want to do.
2. Open the folder for your coding agent.
3. Copy the guide into your agent instructions file or paste it into your agent chat.
4. Ask the agent to help with your Caracal setup in your own codebase.

Use `sdks` when adding Caracal to app code, and `compliance` to review a codebase. To connect a provider, model a resource, or author access policies, use the [Caracal Operator](https://docs.caracal.run/concepts/operator/) in the web console.
